cholars in the field to address this dilemma on several levels. In thirteen original essays, contributors establish a framework for understanding the current crisis, provide historical perspective on the present, offer a stark overview of the day-to-day realities on campuses, and illustrate the role and impact of university leadership. With a foreword by Donald B. Pope-Davis and an afterword by Valerie Kinloch, as well as an introduction by the editors, the volume is provocative, up-to-date, and solution-driven, giving readers both a comprehensive analysis of the racial crisis in American higher education and ideas for addressing it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aCollege integrationzUnited States. 0aDiscrimination in higher educationzUnited States. 0aMinoritiesxEducation (Higher)zUnited States. 0aRacism in higher educationzUnited States. 4aAfrican American Studies : African American Studies. 4aEducation : Educational Administration. 4aEducation : Higher Education. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Walter R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowman, Phillip J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChilders-McKee, Cherese, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChing, Cheryl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCole, Eddie R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbreo, Angela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEzikwelu, Evelyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGutierrez, Rose Ann Rico Eborda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolland, Nia D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/r